# LL-001
# Title:     SQLAlchemy DeclarativeBase reserves 'metadata' as a class attribute
# Milestone: M2
# Source:    ISS-001
# Lesson:    Never name a SQLAlchemy model column 'metadata'.  DeclarativeBase
#            exposes cls.metadata as the table MetaData object; any column with
#            that name raises InvalidRequestError at class definition time.
#            Pattern: rename the Python attribute (e.g. event_metadata) and use
#            Column("metadata", ...) to preserve the DB column name.
# Apply to:  M2, all future milestones that define ORM models

---
# LL-002
# Title:     SQLAlchemy @validates fires at construction time, not at commit
# Milestone: M2
# Source:    ISS-002
# Lesson:    @validates intercepts attribute assignment during the model
#            __init__ call.  pytest.raises must wrap the constructor call, not
#            just session.commit(), to catch validation errors.  Wrap all three:
#            construction, session.add(), and session.commit() inside a single
#            pytest.raises context.
# Apply to:  M2, any future milestone that adds @validates constraints

---
# LL-003
# Title:     Accumulator pattern must preserve @pytest.fixture decorators
# Milestone: M2
# Source:    ISS-003
# Lesson:    When merging or regenerating conftest.py via an accumulator
#            approach, always verify that every fixture function retains the
#            @pytest.fixture decorator.  Plain function definitions are not
#            registered by pytest.  Prefer a full rewrite over incremental
#            appending to avoid silent omissions.
# Apply to:  M2, M3, and all future milestones that add test fixtures

---
# LL-004
# Title:     Hand-crafted ULID test values must be counted to exactly 26 chars
# Milestone: M2
# Source:    ISS-004
# Lesson:    ULIDs are exactly 26 Crockford Base32 characters.  When writing
#            test ULIDs by hand (e.g. "01HQAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA"), count
#            carefully: 4-char timestamp prefix + 22 repeated characters = 26.
#            A common off-by-one is using 23 repeated chars for 27 total.
#            Use the formula: prefix(4) + padding(22) = 26.
# Apply to:  M2, M3, and all future milestones that declare test ULIDs

---
# LL-005
# Title:     SQLAlchemy integration tests need SAVEPOINT isolation with module-scoped engines
# Milestone: M2
# Source:    ISS-005
# Lesson:    When using a module-scoped SQLAlchemy engine (schema created once)
#            with per-test sessions, use SAVEPOINT isolation to prevent test
#            data from persisting across tests.  Pattern:
#              connection = engine.connect()
#              transaction = connection.begin()
#              session = Session(bind=connection)
#              nested = connection.begin_nested()  -- SAVEPOINT
#              yield session
#              session.close(); nested.rollback(); transaction.rollback(); connection.close()
#            Inside fixtures, use session.flush() not session.commit() to avoid
#            committing past the SAVEPOINT boundary.
# Apply to:  M2, all future integration milestones using SQLAlchemy

