# LL-007
# Title:     pydantic-core native binary may not load in cross-arch/cross-version sandboxes
# Milestone: M4
# Source:    ISS-006
# Lesson:    When pydantic-core falls back to its pure-Python stub (detectable by
#            importing pydantic_core._pydantic_core_stub without ImportError),
#            runtime Field constraint enforcement (ge, le, min_length, etc.) is
#            silently disabled and frozen-model equality may fail with AttributeError.
#            Test adaptation pattern:
#            - For constraint tests: inspect model_fields[name].metadata instead of
#              expecting ValidationError at construction time.
#            - For equality: compare model.model_dump() dictionaries, not model objects.
# Apply to:  M4 and all future milestones that test Pydantic model constraints

