# LL-008
# Title:     FastAPI response_model serialization fails silently with pydantic-core stub
# Milestone: M5
# Source:    M5-S4 GREEN implementation
# Lesson:    When pydantic-core native binary is unavailable (cross-arch sandbox),
#            FastAPI's response_model= serialization pipeline calls pydantic-core
#            under the hood and produces an empty {} body instead of raising an error.
#            Two-part workaround for route handlers:
#            (1) Remove response_model= from the @router.get decorator entirely.
#            (2) Replace the return type annotation with JSONResponse.
#            (3) Call model.model_dump() explicitly and return JSONResponse(content=...).
#            Additional: model_construct() must be used instead of Model() for any
#            Pydantic model that contains Optional[str] fields, since the stub raises
#            "TypeError: typing.Optional[str] is not a generic class" at validation time.
#            Always add explicit int(param) coercion when using model_construct()
#            because FastAPI query string params arrive as strings without coercion.
# Apply to:  M5 and all future milestones that return Pydantic models from FastAPI routes

