# LL-009
# Title:     ruff and mypy binaries are architecture-specific and fail in cross-arch VM
# Milestone: M5
# Source:    M5-S5 Quality Gate
# Lesson:    The ruff and mypy wheel binaries installed in .venv are compiled for
#            macOS arm64 (the host), but the sandbox runs Linux x86_64.  The OS
#            returns "Exec format error" when trying to execute them.  Neither
#            python -m ruff nor python -m mypy work for the same reason (the
#            .so extension module inside the wheel is the wrong arch).
#            Workaround: use python ast.parse() for syntax validation, black for
#            formatting, and rely on pytest for behavioural coverage.  Static
#            analysis must be run on the host machine (macOS) where the correct
#            arch binaries are installed.  Document this in CI setup: cross-arch
#            sandbox cannot substitute for host-side type checking.
# Apply to:  M5 and all future milestones — do not attempt ruff/mypy in the sandbox

