# LL-010
# Title:     FastAPI query-param int coercion fails in cross-arch pydantic-core sandbox
# Milestone: M6
# Source:    ISS-015
# Lesson:    When pydantic-core is unavailable (cross-arch sandbox), FastAPI cannot
#            coerce Query() parameters from their raw string form to int.  Default
#            values (Python int literals) arrive correctly, but values supplied in
#            the HTTP query string (e.g. ?offset=1) arrive as str even when the
#            Query() annotation specifies int.  Symptom: TypeError inside the
#            repository on slice operations like list[offset : offset + limit].
#            Fix: add explicit int() casts in the route handler before forwarding
#            params to the repository:
#                result = repo.list(limit=int(limit), offset=int(offset), ...)
#            This is a specialisation of LL-007/LL-008 and applies to all route
#            handlers that accept numeric query parameters.
# Apply to:  M6 and all future milestones that use int Query() parameters

---
# LL-011
# Title:     str-enum model_dump() branches are unreachable — use pragma: no cover
# Milestone: M6
# Source:    M6-S5 Quality Gate
# Lesson:    When a Pydantic model field is typed as a str-enum (class Foo(str, Enum)),
#            model_dump() already serialises it to the string value directly.
#            Defensive guards like:
#                if hasattr(raw["field"], "value"):
#                    raw["field"] = raw["field"].value
#            are logically unreachable and will never be covered by tests.
#            Add # pragma: no cover to such branches rather than writing artificial
#            tests that cannot actually trigger them.  This prevents false coverage
#            failures and makes the intent clear to future maintainers.
# Apply to:  M6 and all future milestones that include serialization helpers

