# LL-012
# Title:     Optional[StrEnum] pydantic-core validation fails when value is non-None
# Milestone: M7
# Source:    M7-S4 GREEN — _build_equity_response() in charts.py
# Lesson:    The cross-arch pydantic-core stub raises:
#            "TypeError: typing.Optional[libs.contracts.chart.SamplingMethod]
#             is not a generic class"
#            when constructing a Pydantic model whose Optional[str-Enum] field
#            is assigned a non-None enum value.  The same field with None passes
#            silently (the stub short-circuits validation for None).
#            Symptom: tests for the LTTB-applied code path fail; tests for the
#            no-sampling code path pass.  Diagnosis: sampling_method=None vs
#            sampling_method=SamplingMethod.LTTB triggers the stub's type-checking.
#            Fix: use model_construct() instead of Model() for any Pydantic model
#            that contains an Optional[str-Enum] field and may be populated with
#            a non-None value in the cross-arch sandbox:
#                return EquityChartResponse.model_construct(
#                    sampling_method=SamplingMethod.LTTB, ...
#                )
#            Note: this is a refinement of LL-007 — LL-007 covered Optional[str],
#            LL-012 covers Optional[str-Enum] specifically.
# Apply to:  M7 and all future milestones with Optional[Enum] Pydantic fields

